hereby triggers flowering.<\/p>\n  \n  <p>......<\/p>\n  \n  <p>We propose that early in the day phyB promotes the degradation of CO whereas in the evening cryptochromes and phyA antagonize this degradation and stabilize CO protein, <\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>However, my knowledge of plant molecular biology is not that great and I would advise that you refer the mentioned article and the cross references cited in that.  <\/p>\n","answer_id":8105,"question_id":8099,"up_vote_count":2}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/8099/how-do-animals-plants-change-for-each-season","last_activity_date":1376099494,"creation_date":1367033721,"answer_count":1,"title":"How do animals/plants change for each season?","body":"<p>The question pretty much sums it up. How do animals/plants change for each: Spring, Summer, Autumn, and Winter? <\/p>\n\n<p>A detailed explanation on distinct behaviour and appearance changes would be nice.<\/p>\n","question_id":8099,"tags":["zoology","botany","ethology","life-history","phenology"],"score":1,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":411,"up_vote_count":1,"last_edit_date":1376099494},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/f0PGT.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":3615,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3615/biogirl","reputation":3923,"display_name":"biogirl","accept_rate":89},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/6de2ee4a7f7e3323daea4eb795260f47?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":1853,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1853/keegan-keplinger","reputation":688,"display_name":"Keegan Keplinger"},"score":3,"is_accepted":true,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/f0PGT.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":3615,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3615/biogirl","reputation":3923,"display_name":"biogirl","accept_rate":89},"score":0,"post_id":9697,"edited":false,"creation_