 wolves were present?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d2ecbadc57c0e7692ff27ec985b64af0?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":839,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/839/odp","reputation":240,"display_name":"ODP","accept_rate":25},"score":0,"post_id":2295,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8729233d525a654914051bf8c1234c78?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":115,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/115/nico","reputation":6011,"display_name":"nico","accept_rate":100},"edited":false,"creation_date":1337275434,"comment_id":3072,"body":"Would you say my reason seems unreasonable?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/fdd630f72eef3790bfb4ef38d08c7f85?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":166,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/166/konrad-rudolph","reputation":3847,"display_name":"Konrad Rudolph"},"score":2,"post_id":2295,"edited":false,"creation_date":1337299413,"comment_id":3081,"body":"@Olly Your reasons are in fact spot-on but if I remember correctly (but it might have been another of his books), Dakwins explicitly mentions that in order for changes to occur so fast, the variability in the genome has to be already present."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d2ecbadc57c0e7692ff27ec985b64af0?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":839,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/839/odp","reputation":240,"display_name":"ODP","accept_rate":25},"score":0,"post_id":2295,"edited":false,"creation_date":1337338213,"comment_id":3089,"body":"That would make perfect sense, I couldn&#39;t imagine it happening in such short time if there wasn&#39;t variability in the genome, thank you."}],"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/08613e0b782cdf2bb8f2501cae9bdc5d?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":806,"link":"