es, and even catalyze reactions between small molecules. <a href=\"http://www.scs.illinois.edu/silverman/research/index.html\">See this lab's website.<\/a><\/p>\n","answer_id":8998,"question_id":8996,"up_vote_count":10},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/79c5c049a14868e4f7510fb035cb61f2?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":4175,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4175/user2651043","reputation":54,"display_name":"user2651043"},"score":0,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/KD6Fx.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":3952,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3952/oreotrephes","reputation":4267,"display_name":"Oreotrephes","accept_rate":86},"score":1,"post_id":9627,"edited":false,"creation_date":1375697836,"comment_id":12671,"body":"Could you give a bit more detail here? It&#39;s hard to tell what you&#39;re referring to."}],"down_vote_count":0,"last_activity_date":1375688631,"creation_date":1375688631,"body":"<p>Yes, maintenance of the genome.  But not DNA specifically, but DNA and all of its associated proteins.<\/p>\n","answer_id":9627,"question_id":8996,"up_vote_count":0},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4e372c4b94e6de48fc11bbc1e57f4e36?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":4177,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4177/gchadwick","reputation":1011,"display_name":"gchadwick"},"score":1,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/KD6Fx.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":3952,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3952/oreotrephes","reputation":4267,"display_name":"Oreotrephes","accept_rate":86},"score":1,"post_id":9629,"edited":false,"creation_date":1375697905,"comment_id":12672,"body":"Interesting! Can you give a reference?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4e372c4b94e6de48fc11bbc1e57f4e36?s=128